item.title: Some easy 614 questions
item.dc:creator: @QuestMaster_2K10 QuestMaster 2K10
item.description:
@QuestMaster_2K10 wrote:

Ints for custom would probably be handled client-side in files. If you can’t find the files, then it’s possibly compressed in the cache and you’ll need some tools to decompress it to get the files out to modify them, and the recompress it back into the cache.

As for making yourself owner, open the file that has your username possibly with the extension ‘.ser’ or whatever you said. If this is correct, then right-click it, and click “Open with…”, and then select “Notepad” as the default program to open the file with. Then find where it says “rights” and wherever the number is after that change to two.
